  "why": "The paper's method (CrossASR) uses differential testing by cross-referencing multiple ASRs at once to detect disagreements and trains a failure-probability classifier using labels derived from those multi-ASR outcomes. However, it does not include an explicit design to discover transferable attacks (e.g., crafting inputs against a surrogate model) nor does it evaluate whether fault-inducing inputs discovered for one model are reused to induce failures in other, separately-held target models. All experiments feed the same TTS-generated audio to multiple ASRs simultaneously and report per-ASR failure counts, but do not perform or report transfer experiments where inputs found on one model are applied to a different unseen target.",
